      • save

        public void save(IEntity entity)
          throws TresosDBException
        Saves a non persistent entity recursively to the database.

        If this TresosDB has a root entity, the given entity must match the root entity. If this does not have a root entity yet, the given one becomes the root entity.

        This also works for TresosDBs with Mode.MEMORY and dbFile set. In this case, the Mode is switched to Mode.CREATE and the entity is saved.
        ATTENTION: Calling this with an existing dbFile set will overwrite the file without further confirmation!

        For an already persistent entity this method does nothing as the state of each persistent entity is saved immediately on change.
        Parameters:
        entity - The entity to save
        Throws:
        TresosDBException - This Exception is thrown by the tresosDB to indicate invalid calls to API functions.
        Since:
        2008.b

      • save

        public void save(java.io.File dbFile,
                 IEntity entity)
          throws TresosDBException
        Saves an entity recursively to the given database file.

        If this TresosDB has a root entity, the given entity must match the root entity. If this does not have a root entity yet, the given one becomes the root entity.

        If this TresosDB is already file based (i.e. the mode is Mode.CREATE or Mode.OPEN), the old file is closed and copied to the given location. All further operations of the TresosDB are executed using the new file.

        If this TresosDB is an in-memory database (i.e. the mode is Mode.MEMORY), the given file is used as dbFile, the mode is switched to Mode.CREATE and the entity is saved.

        ATTENTION: Calling this with an existing file will overwrite the file without further confirmation!
        Parameters:
        dbFile - The file to save the entity to
        entity - The entity to save
        Throws:
        TresosDBException - This Exception is thrown by the tresosDB to indicate invalid calls to API functions.
        Since:
        10.0
